gomodel:SYNGO_2938  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"SV Endocytosis Is Driven by Formin-Mediated Actin Assembly and Myosin II Activity in Hippocampal Neurons\"\n- \"shRNA-mediated knockdown of the diaphanous-related formin mDia1 (Figures S3C and S3D), a formin isoform present in neurons including synapses (Figures S3E-S3G) and previously implicated in endocytic pathways in non-neuronal cells (Gasman et al., 2003; Levayer et al., 2011), slowed the kinetics of SV endocytosis similar to formin inhibition by SMIFH2 (Figures 3L and 3M). These data indicate that mDia1, and, possibly, other formin family members mediate F-actin assembly to regulate SV endocytosis.\". Experimental description: - \"Neuronal cultures were prepared by surgically removing the hippocampi from postnatal mice ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2938" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

